OL,4,CDying Bill
OL,6,FMSPs will vote this evening on the
OL,7,Ffirst stage of a bill which could
OL,8,Flegalise assisted dying in Scotland.
OL,10,FThe bill, piloted by Liberal Democrat
OL,11,FMSP Liam McArthur, would allow
OL,12,Fterminally ill people deemed mentally
OL,13,Fcapable to choose to end their own
OL,14,Flives.
OL,16,FIf it passes, the Assisted Dying for
OL,17,FTerminally Ill Adults (Scotland) Bill
OL,18,Fwill progress to the next stage in
OL,19,Fparliament.
