OL,6,FMany MSPs have suggested they may back
OL,7,Fthe general principles of the
OL,8,Flegislation but would want to see
OL,9,Fchanges made before the next vote.
OL,11,FA number of high profile politicians
OL,12,Fin Scotland have already said they
OL,13,Fwill not support the Bill, including
OL,14,Fthe First Minister John Swinney,
OL,15,Fdeputy first minister Kate Forbes and
OL,16,Fthe former first ministers Nicola
OL,17,FSturgeon and Humza Yousaf.
OL,19,FAt Holyrood today, campaigners who are
OL,20,Fboth for and against the move held
OL,21,Fdemonstrations.
