OL,6,FHe said: "The problem is that you're
OL,7,Factually saying the NHS has a license
OL,8,Fto kill and that's what it really
OL,9,Fcomes down to. If this bill was to
OL,10,Fbecome law then it almost puts medical
OL,11,Fprofessionals in the place of playing
OL,12,FGod and I think that's very dangerous.
OL,14,FMark's father died 18 months ago, at
OL,15,Fthe age of 98. He says he may have
OL,16,Ffelt pressured to choose an assisted
OL,17,Fdeath, had it been an option.
OL,19,F"He had a lot of help from the NHS, he
OL,20,Fwent through bowel cancer and they
OL,21,Fsuccessfully operated.
