OL,6,FMajor concerns remain about vulnerable
OL,7,Fpeople being coerced into an early
OL,8,Fdeath, the prospect of an expansion
OL,9,Fbeyond the current parameters of the
OL,10,Flegislation happening with limited
OL,11,Foversight and even the fact that
OL,12,FHolyrood does not have all the powers
OL,13,Fto enact this without support from
OL,14,FWestminster.
OL,16,FIt is entirely possible that support
OL,17,Ftonight will melt away as the
OL,18,Fparliamentary process continues and
OL,19,Fthe backing is temporary.
