OL,6,FLikewise, opposition from the likes of
OL,7,FLabour MSP Pam Duncan-Glancy and
OL,8,FConservative MSP Edward Mountain `
OL,9,Fboth of which have personal reasons on
OL,10,Ftop of their policy concerns ` has
OL,11,Fbeen put forward in a measured manner
OL,12,Fthat shows you do not need to be
OL,13,Faggressive to stand your ground.
OL,15,FIt may or may not be third time lucky
OL,16,Ffor the assisted dying bill but voters
OL,17,Fare fortunate that such a
OL,18,Fcontroversial issue is being examined
OL,19,Fcarefully and with consideration
OL,20,Frather than being swept into culture
OL,21,Fwars.
